{{Politics of Denmark}}
'''Parliamentary elections''' were held in [[Denmark]] on 12 December 1990.<ref name=DN>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen, D]] & StÃ¶ver, P (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p525 ISBN 9873832956097</ref> Although the election resulted in a strong gain for the [[Social Democrats (Denmark)|Social Democratic Party]], [[Poul SchlÃ¼ter]]'s coalition government was able to continue despite the [[Danish Social Liberal Party]] leaving. SchlÃ¼ter's coalition consisted of the [[Conservative People's Party (Denmark)|Conservative People's Party]] and [[Venstre (Denmark)|Venstre]]. Voter turnout was 82.8% in Denmark proper, 54.4% in the [[Faroe Islands]] and 50.8% in [[Greenland]].<ref name=NS>Nohlen & StÃ¶ver, p548</ref>
